Troubleshooting Theory

Steps 
1. Identify the problem
2. Established a theory of probable cause
	- asked questions 
3. Test the theory to determime probable cause
4. Establishing a plan of Action and test the Solution
5. Verifying Full system functinality
6. Documents your findings 

NOTES > Troubleshooting technical problem is core to a Tech's job
	  > Listening to your users is a critical part of troubleshooting
	  > remember the steps to comptia's troubleshooting process